title: Chapter 2 - Thread and Locks
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Thread and locks tend to be difficult, unreliable and dangerous compared to newer stuff. Yet they tend to be the default choice.
They are little more than a formalization of what the underlying hardware does; Hence they are supported almost everywhere, but does not provide general design guideline, so programmer can find himself quickly dealing with a lovecraftian horror.